<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idca913d48-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s2434"><num value="2434">§ 2434.</num><heading> Termination of authority</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idca913d49-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s2434/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Subject to subsection (b), the authority of the Secretary to carry out this subchapter terminates on the date that is 10 years after <date date="2006-12-22">December 22, 2006</date>.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idca913d4a-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s2434/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Exception</heading><chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The termination of authority under subsection (a) shall have no effect on—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idca913d4b-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s2434/b/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> any loans guaranteed by the United States under this subchapter; or</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idca913d4c-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s2434/b/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> the administration of any loan guaranteed under this subchapter before the effective date of the termination of authority.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idca913d4d-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/451/tII/s215">Pub. L. 109–451, title II, § 215</ref>, <date date="2006-12-22">Dec. 22, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/3361">120 Stat. 3361</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
